}
```

Usage:

```rust
fn main() {
    timed!("fn main");              // scope guard, prints on drop

    timed!("parsing args", {        // block, prints after body
        let cli = Cli::parse();
    });
}
```

One macro, two forms. The call site makes the intent obvious. And you can drop `timed_new!`.

